               "text": "### Images from UNESCO\n\nThese images are copyright for UNESCO and allowed to be used according to the license determined by them.\n\nTo visualize all images, use the left and right arrows on the slide below.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 5</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgLAMSE\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgLAMSE', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Archaeological National Site of L'Anse aux Meadows. Photo by Dick Houghton, available on the UNESCO website (<htcite0>). Shared under license <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/2.0/deed.en\" target=\"_blank\">Attribution-Noncommercial 2.0 Generic</a>.</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Who truly discovered America (<i>Abya Yala</i>)? (Who... ?)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">2 / 5</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgUNESCO\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgUNESCO', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Altamira Cave and Paleolithic Cave Art of Northern Spain. Photo by Yvon Fruneau. © UNESCO (<htcite1>). Shared under the <a href=\"https://whc.unesco.org/en/licenses/6\" target=\"_blank\">Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 IGO</a> license.</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Understanding Texts: Grouping texts - A text is more than just a sequence of words. In this study, we begin to examine ancient texts in detail, aiming to understand the elements that compose them. (<htcite6>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">3 / 5</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgWALL\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgWALL', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Great Zimbabwe National Monument (<htcite2>). Photograph taken by Erik Eschweiler-Dienerowitz and made available on the UNESCO website (<htcite3>). Shared under the <a href=\"https://whc.unesco.org/en/licenses/6\" target=\"_blank\">Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 IGO</a> license.</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Atlas: Great Zimbabwe - civilization built by the Shona people, one of the Bantu-speaking groups, in Zimbabwe. (<htcite7>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">4 / 5</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgCW\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgCW', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Great Wall of China. Photo by Giovanni Boccardi, available on the UNESCO website (<htcite4>). Shared under license <a href=\"https://whc.unesco.org/en/licenses/6\" target=\"_blank\">Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 IGO</a>.</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>History: Culture and Civilization - Is there a hierarchy between them? (<htcite8>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">5 / 5</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgBI\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgBI', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Behistun Inscription. Photo taken by Babak Sedighi and made available on the UNESCO website (<htcite5>). Shared under the <a href=\"https://whc.unesco.org/en/licenses/6\" target=\"_blank\">Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 IGO</a> license.</div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
